                            <comment id="14703085" author="sgehwolf" created="Thu, 5 Sep 2024 09:00:17 -0700"  >Critical fix request (OpenJDK 17u):&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Please approve this compatibility fix to get to pre JDK 17.0.11 state. Critical fix so as to improve compatibility already in 17.0.13. On some Linux systems where birth time is supported - the statx system call is available - but the filesystem doesn&amp;#39;t support birth time (e.g. NFS or tmpfs on older kernels) the epoch (0) used to be returned. With this patch on such unsupported FS it behaves as if birth time wasn&amp;#39;t supported at all and returns the last modified time of the file instead. Risk should be low. CSR has been approved. There is the known issue with the test (&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8338884&quot; title=&quot;java/nio/file/attribute/BasicFileAttributeView/CreationTime.java#tmp fails on alinux3&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8338884&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8338884&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) and a problem on older Docker versions related to seccomp and the statx syscall (&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8337966&quot; title=&quot;(fs) Files.readAttributes fails with Operation not permitted on older docker releases&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8337966&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8337966&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). This patch doesn&amp;#39;t change that. Manual tests work as expected (see comments in the backport bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8339476&quot; title=&quot;(fs) BasicFileAttributes.creationTime() falls back to epoch if birth time is unavailable (Linux)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8339476&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8339476&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). NIO tests pass the same before and after the patch.</comment>
                            <comment id="14703051" author="sgehwolf" created="Thu, 5 Sep 2024 06:40:59 -0700"  >Critical fix request (OpenJDK 21u):&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Please approve this compatibility fix to get to pre JDK 21.0.2 state. Critical fix so as to improve compatibility already in 21.0.5 (Oracle JDK 21 backed it out). On some Linux systems where birth time is supported - the statx system call is available - but the filesystem doesn&amp;#39;t support birth time (e.g. NFS or tmpfs on older kernels) the epoch (0) used to be returned. With this patch on such unsupported FS it behaves as if birth time wasn&amp;#39;t supported at all and returns the last modified time of the file instead. Risk should be low. CSR has been approved. There is the known issue with the test (&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8338884&quot; title=&quot;java/nio/file/attribute/BasicFileAttributeView/CreationTime.java#tmp fails on alinux3&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8338884&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8338884&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) and a problem on older Docker versions related to seccomp and the statx syscall (&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8337966&quot; title=&quot;(fs) Files.readAttributes fails with Operation not permitted on older docker releases&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8337966&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8337966&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Manual tests work as expected (see comments in the backport bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8339372&quot; title=&quot;(fs) BasicFileAttributes.creationTime() falls back to epoch if birth time is unavailable (Linux)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8339372&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8339372&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). NIO tests pass the same before and after the patch.</comment>
